Introduction
Artificial turf, commonly known as synthetic grass, has become a popular alternative to natural grass in various applications, ranging from sports fields to landscaping. It offers a low-maintenance, cost-effective, and durable solution for areas where natural grass may be challenging to maintain due to environmental conditions or heavy usage. The global artificial turf market is witnessing steady growth, driven by increasing adoption in sports infrastructure, residential and commercial landscaping, and the rising need for water conservation.
This article provides a detailed overview of the artificial turf market, including its definition, market dynamics, key players, segmentation, recent developments, opportunities and challenges, regional analysis, and frequently asked questions (FAQs).
